  "text": "The Kafka consumer heartbeat session timeout mechanism works as follows:\n\n1. **Threshold Definition**: The session timeout threshold is defined as a configurable parameter:\n   - CommonClientConfigs.java (line 207) defines the configuration key SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG = \"session.timeout.ms\" with documentation explaining it is \"The timeout used to detect client failures when using Kafka's group management facility.\"\n   - GroupRebalanceConfig.java (line 52) reads this configuration value using config.getInt(CommonClientConfigs.SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG) and stores it in the sessionTimeoutMs field.\n\n2. **Timer Creation and Management**: \n   - Heartbeat.java (line 52) creates a Timer object with the session timeout value: sessionTimer = time.timer(config.sessionTimeoutMs)\n   - The sessionTimeoutExpired() method (lines 119-122) checks if this timer has expired\n\n3. **Timeout Detection and Logging During Consumer Polling Loop**:\n   - AbstractCoordinator.java contains the heartbeatThread (lines 1480+) which runs in a background thread and continuously polls for heartbeat timeouts\n   - At line 1513, the code checks: heartbeat.sessionTimeoutExpired(now)\n   - When this condition is true (session timeout has expired), line 1516-1517 calls markCoordinatorUnknown(\"session timed out without receiving a \" + \"heartbeat response\")\n   - The markCoordinatorUnknown method (lines 1004-1028) logs the timeout event at line 1006: log.info(\"Group coordinator {} is unavailable or invalid due to cause: {}. isDisconnected: {}. Rediscovery will be attempted.\", ...)\n\nThis chain shows how a heartbeat session timeout is detected during the consumer polling loop and properly logged, causing the consumer to drop membership and attempt to rediscover the group coordinator."
}

